No , logically, fairly and truthfully, Adesanya shouldnt win this award (so glad he didn't) people saying Adesanya was fighter of the year , did NOT take into consideration much of what he did THIS year , they took into consideration what he did in his Career , if it's just THIS year , then would you pick a guy who finished only 1 fight out of 3 and also won the belt , fought a 44 year old broken footed Anderson, OR would you pick a guy who finished 3 of 3 and got a new special belt just for him and also got the fastest K.O. of the year vs an fighter whom was undefeated in 2 major promotions, stopping the Hype train Till in his home town , and beat the sheit out of diaz (which in 2 matches McGregor couldn't do)?


Adesanya deserves fight of the years vs Gastellum and that's it , be happy with that and stfu , it's Masvidal time bitches.


Also , to ppl who think Adesanya's decision over Anderson is something to be proud of.....dude....he's forty fucking four years old , Cannonier hit him a few times in the leg the next match and he broke anderson in half a fucking round :)))) , anderson after he broke his foot to Weidman was always at 50% or less of his original prowess , so please stfu , be beat a guy who can literally be a grandparent and had one of the worst leg injuries i've seen in combat sports...and he didn't even finish him :P


P.S. Anderson lost 7 of his last 8(oficially 6 of 8 but since he got caught with 3 different PEDs after the Diaz fight , i will give that win to Diaz easily), so you arguing he is the same is mental retardism, he is barely half the man he was.

His performances this year were simply shocking and incredibly uncannily fulfilling hype, so the impact was even more. However. He is simply not the fighter of the year. usman could easily be considered fighter of the year with the names that he has knocked off, and certainly Adesanya. Every single fight that Adesanya has fought was harder than Masvidal's. He just makes it look easy but he is in another stratosphere from Masvidal, and so is the hill that he had to climb to get that belt.

snippet.textDisplay: No offense to Jorge, but this should've been Izzy's award.  He's beaten the top guys in the division,  and I don't think Jorge can beat Gastelum or Whitaker.
